          "population": "862750",
          "descriptionFromReview": "You gotta be kidding me.. i lived in Fortaleza for 5 years. Safety is almost non existent, only in 1-2 limited neighborhoods. There are not so many things to do in the city and you can only walk around beiramar beach, otherwise you have to take an uber because you feel unsafe while walking. You see nobody on the streets but beggers. The hospitals are the worst public ones usually don't have a doctor, and private ones has long queues besides expensive price you pay, the city is dirty, the main beach was infested with rats just last month. It's kinda cheap but the quality of life is bad and not worth living there. It's only a good spot for a week if you enjoy beach imo.",
