          "image_lastmod": 1661559146,
          "region": "Oceania",
          "population": "540559",
          "descriptionFromReview": "My partner and I lived in Gold Coast  for 6 months during the coronavirus pandemic. Its a very expensive place to live and its hard to find optimal housing. There are many Austrialians looking to live here so its has a growing housing market, we experienced a rental rate increase during our stay.   This seems to be a lively city with many visitors and fun amusement parks, clubs, and nice shopping centers. But for us the main value was its proximity to a world class beach. This is THE nicest city beach I have ever experienced and its hard to compare to anywhere else, tall expensive skyscrapers with luxurious white sand and big surfable waves was the highlights of our stay.",
